# This config is automatically loaded after the built-in `rc` file, if the
# $NO_COLOR enviroment variable is set (and non-empty) at startup. All of
# the syntax highlighting styles defined in `color/default` are retained,
# since $NO_COLOR also makes the `syntax` option default to false (and we
# want to allow toggling it with e.g. `toggle syntax`). Thus, all we do
# here is override some previously set UI colors that don't fall into the
# category of "sparing" usage (as mentioned at https://no-color.org/).

hi noline dim
hi selection reverse
hi errormsg bold
hi infomsg
hi dialog reverse
